      • boundValueToAttributeLimits

        public double boundValueToAttributeLimits(double value,
                                          Attribute a)

        Takes a value and checks if it belongs to the attribute interval. If not, it returns the nearest limit. IT DOES NOT CHECK IF THE ATTRIBUTE IS NOT NOMINAL

        Parameters:
        value - the value to be checked
        a - the attribute to which the value will be checked against
        Returns:
        the original value if it was in the interval limits of the attribute, or the nearest boundary limit otherwise.
